article.headline: UNC Greensboro 79, St. Peter's 58
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. (AP) -- Ricky Hickman scored a game-high 28 points and Kyle Hines had a double-double with 19 points and 14 rebounds to lead UNC Greensboro to a 79-58 victory over St. Peter's on Thursday. The Spartans (4-6) were ahead 8-7 before going on a 24-0 run midway through the first half to make it 32-7, holding the Peacocks scoreless for eight minutes. St. Peter's opened the game by missing 16 of its first 18 shots from the floor. The Peacocks got within eight in the second half, but UNC Greensboro pulled away late for the easy win. Kevin Spann scored 20 points to lead Saint Peter's (3-7), while Raul Orta added 17.
